# Early-return resource cleanup

## Rule

Any early exit before normal cleanup must perform equivalent cleanup or move
cleanup into a `finally`/shared helper.

## Resources to check

- Temp files and directories.
- Staged uploads/downloads/exports.
- Locks, leases, transactions, savepoints, advisory locks.
- Queued jobs and reservation rows.
- Streams, file handles, sockets, browser contexts, workers.
- DB status rows and audit records.
- UI loading, optimistic, and pending states.

## Pre-commit check

- [ ] Every new `return`, `continue`, `break`, or `throw` before cleanup was reviewed.
- [ ] Cleanup is centralized or duplicated intentionally.
- [ ] Tests cover the early-exit path.
